reviews.review_text: short fingers and playing nice peter and he's gone jams, set seems to get better as it goes, sound of highs a bit glassy
Great Peter Thanx Scott.  Nice audience recording and a nice upgrade from my incomplete cassette.  1st half is low key and 2nd half is a good cooker with an amazing Peter.  Peace

A mediocre show for my mediocre... 34th birthday. Not that it matters but since I saw many folks write reviews about shows just because it was on their birthday, and in some cases, they didn't even go to. I thought I'd mention that, (actually, my birthday is the day before but this is the closest they ever came to it); since it obviously has no bearing on the show itself.
Another reason I mention it, and this is just speculation, I wondered why, since they were so tight with Bill Graham, for Bob Weir to claim on 1978-1-8 in San Diego, a show I was at, and if your not familiar with, I highly recommend, that they didn't know it was his birthday apparently until shortly before, he announced that because of this short notice they couldn't get him anything, therefore they, (as he said, or was it really just he), was going to give him a new name, the now infamous "Uncle Bobo" that Bill Graham said he didn't really like, but it stuck to some extent, at least in some circles.
So I thought if it was true, that that was the first time they'd been around Bill Graham on his birthday, how could that be ? Well, the only thing I could reason is the same reason they never played on my "real" birthday, (or even to my knowledge, on my birthday before I first saw them, or far away from me); that is, in general there are few years (very early years, '78 and these final years. (? I have to double check the last two), in which they ever played much in January !

     Augy

     San Diego

Augy's an idiot!! Can anyone tell me if "Augy" was born an idiot, or has he/she been workin' @ it?? Either way, it seems to have worked out just fine!!! I thought the show was just FINE!! But, maybe I'm partial... I only followed the boys for 20 years!!!

This show deserves a higher rating We all can agree the caliber of play dropped off as the '90's wore on. Having attended 200+ shows, including this one, my opinion carries some weight. This show sounded awesome in the Coliseum, I stood just to the right of the soundboard, and this tape captures it pretty well. The jam in Crazy Fingers and the Black Peter are deluxe and worth a listen. I particularly remember the Peter delivering the goods live- it was one of those moments, people were looking at each other, knowing they got something.
